<h2>Christ the Reconciler</h2>
<p>A Missional Community of Reconciliation involving Protestants, Catholic, Orthodox, and Messianics Jews</p>

<p>Our goal is to live out John 17, Jesus' only prayer for all his people.</p>

<p>The Problem is not Division; The Problem is Hostility</p>
<p>Hostility between followers of Jesus runs rampant.</p>

<p>We express contempt for one another from the pulpit. Outbursts of anger explode on social media. Even acts of physical violence are not unheard of.</p>

<p>The world watches and writes off our witness of Jesus.</p>
<p>Jesus’ answer to hostility is Reconciliation</p>
<p>Reconciliation is a series of actions that removes hostility in a relationship, repairs the damage it caused, and restores the God-intended unity.</p>
<p>The God-intended unity for His people is for us to enter into the unity of the Trinity!  </p><p>Jesus made this clear in his one prayer for us, recorded in John 17:</p>

<figure>
  <blockquote>
    <p>I pray also for whoever will believe in me through their message, so that they all will be one, Father, just as you are in me and I am in you.</p><p>May they also be one in us so that this world will believe that you sent me into this world.</p>
  </blockquote>
  <figcaption class="source">— Jesus in John 17</figcaption>
</figure>